1/4 cup oil

2 medium potatoes, peeled and coarse diced

2 large carrots, peeled and cubed

1 small onion, peeled and chopped
3 cloves garlic, peeled and minced
1 thumb ginger, peeled and minced

4 lbs chicken, cut

1 Tbsp fish sauce

2 cups coconut milk
1 cup water

1/2 green bell pepper
1/2 red bell pepper

2 Tbsp curry powder


In wide pan over medium heat, heat oil.
Add potatoes; cook 2 to 3 minutes
Remove potatoes.
Add carrots; cook 1 to 2 minutes
Remove carrots.
Add bell peppers; cook 30 to 40 seconds
Remove bell peppers.
Add chicken; cook until browned
Add onions, garlic, ginger; cook until soft
Add 1 Tbsp fish sauce; cook 1 minute
Add 2 cups coconut milk and 1 cup water; bring to simmer, skim scum
Lower heat, cover and simmer 20 to 30 minutes
Add potatoes and carrots; cook 3 to 5 minutes
Add 2 Tbsp curry powder, stir to combine; cook 2 to 3 minutes
Season with salt and pepper to taste
Add bell peppers and cook 1 minute
Serve over rice
